                                              Monster Hunter World:Iceborne Mod Manager Command Line Tool

Why am I write this application?
        Just interesting.

User Interface :
        > mhwimmc
        mhwimmc: Monster Hunter World:Iceborne Mod Manager
        mhwimmc: cd [ path ]
        mhwimmc: ls
        mhwimmc:
                file
                file
                ...
        mhwimmc: install [ mod name ] [ mod path | mod full path]
        mhwimmc: uninstall [ mod name ]
        mhwimmc: installed
                <mod name> <mod path> <date>
                ...
        mhwimmc: set-game-root [ path ]

Mod records :
        sqlite table records.
        [ MOD NAME ] [ MOD PATH ] [ DATE ]
        <mod name>   <mod path>   <date>

Modules :
        [ UI Module ]
        [ Command Module ]
        [ Record Module ]
        [ Config Module ]

    UI Module :
            print console messages
    Command Module :
            read command from user and handles it
    Record Module :
            update data base
    Config Module :
            records some paths

Config file :
        USERHOME => the user's home who first initialized this application
        MHWIROOT => root directory of Monster Hunter World:Iceborne
        MHWIMMCROOT => root directory of mhwimmc
        RECORDSFILE => file name of the file records mod installing info

Threaded :
        three threads >
                1> UI Module
                2> Command Module
                3> Record Module and Config Module
        ! all threads are non-detach

        thread IPC >
                mutex :
                  1> mutex UICmd_mutex for synchronization between UI and Command
                  2> muex CmdRecord_mutex for synchronization between Command and Record
                process memory space :
                  1> UI input and Command output buffer
                     - char memory buffer
                  2> Install/Uninstall record buffer
                     - 
                       struct table record {
                               database op
                               mod name
                               mod install path
                               install date
                       }

Development Environment :
        Language >
                C and C++
        Compiler >
                gcc 10.3.0 and g++ 10.3.0
        GNU/libc >
                glibc 2.31
        Linux >
                linux 5.4.32
        Sqlite >
                sqlite 3
